  def scrape(:xml, "http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor-rss.ashx", mapping) do
    "<?xml version=\"1.0\"?><rss version=\"2.0\"><channel><title>House Floor Proceedings</title><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx</link><description>House Floor proceedings of the previous 1 legislative days, including current legislative days in progress.</description><language>en-US</language><pubDate>Wed, 18 Oct 2017 03:59:48 GMT</pubDate><lastBuildDate>Wed, 18 Oct 2017 03:59:48 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title>Legislative Day Of October 16, 2017  - 10:02:36 A.M.</title><description>\nThe Speaker announced that the House do now adjourn pursuant to section 2(b) of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/562\"&gt;H. Res. 562&lt;/a&gt;. The next meeting is scheduled for 12:00 p.m. on October 19, 2017.\n</description><guid>20171016T10:02:36</guid><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2017 14:03:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20171016</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of October 16, 2017  - 10:02:09 A.M.</title><description>\nThe House received a communication from Tim Murphy, Member of Congress. Pursuant to Rule VIII of the Rules of the U.S. House of Representatives, Mr. Murphy notified the House that he had been served with a subpoena for documents and testimony, issued by the Court of Common Pleas for Allegheny County and that after consultation with the Office of General Counsel, he would make determinations required by Rule VIII.\n</description><guid>20171016T10:02:09</guid><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2017 14:16:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20171016</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of October 16, 2017  - 10:01:26 A.M.</title><description>\nPLEDGE OF ALLEGIANCE - The Chair led the House in reciting the Pledge of Allegiance to the Flag.\n</description><guid>20171016T10:01:26</guid><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2017 14:01:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20171016</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of October 16, 2017  - 10:01:01 A.M.</title><description>\nSPEAKER'S APPROVAL OF THE JOURNAL - Pursuant to section 2(a) of H. Res. 562, the Journal of the last day's proceedings was approved.\n</description><guid>20171016T10:01:01</guid><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2017 14:01:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20171016</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of October 16, 2017  - 10:00:38 A.M.</title><description>\nToday's prayer was offered by Monsignor Stephen Rossetti, Catholic University of America, Washington, DC\n</description><guid>20171016T10:00:38</guid><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2017 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20171016</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of October 16, 2017  - 10:00:22 A.M.</title><description>\nThe Speaker designated the Honorable Rob Woodall to act as Speaker pro tempore for today.\n</description><guid>20171016T10:00:22</guid><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2017 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20171016</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of October 16, 2017  - 10:00:05 A.M.</title><description>\nThe House convened, starting a new legislative day.\n</description><guid>20171016T10:00:05</guid><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2017 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20171016</link></item></channel></rss>"
    |> SweetXml.parse
    |> SweetXml.xmap(mapping)
  end

